mpls.name: mpls

revisions.description: Changed mplsLspName and mplsLspPathName size to 64 from 32 and 16 respectively.
Changed the ORGANIZATION, CONTACT-INFO and DESCRIPTION fields.
Add support for proprietary extensions to the VLL and VPLS mib.

brcdMplsAdminGroupTable.name: brcdMplsAdminGroupTable
brcdMplsAdminGroupTable.description: List of administrative groups (by ID) that have a configured group name.

brcdMplsAdminGroupEntry.name: brcdMplsAdminGroupEntry
brcdMplsAdminGroupEntry.description: Information about an administrative group entry.

brcdMplsAdminGroupId.name: brcdMplsAdminGroupId
brcdMplsAdminGroupId.description: Identifies the administrative group ID in 1-based. The end user of this object must convert this to 0-based since this maps to the bit position in the constraint-based link selection.

brcdMplsAdminGroupName.name: brcdMplsAdminGroupName
brcdMplsAdminGroupName.description: The group name that this administrative group is associated with.

brcdMplsAdminGroupRowStatus.name: brcdMplsAdminGroupRowStatus
brcdMplsAdminGroupRowStatus.description: The row status of an entry. Note: Set request to this table is not supported in this release. Always returns 'active' for the existing entries.

brcdMplsInterfaceEntry.name: brcdMplsInterfaceEntry
brcdMplsInterfaceEntry.description: Information about an MPLS interface entry.

brcdMplsInterfaceIndex.name: brcdMplsInterfaceIndex
brcdMplsInterfaceIndex.description: The ifIndex of the MPLS-enabled port or VE interface.

brcdMplsInterfaceAdminGroup.name: brcdMplsInterfaceAdminGroup
brcdMplsInterfaceAdminGroup.description: Specifies which administrative groups this MPLS-enabled interface belongs to.

brcdMplsInterfaceRowStatus.name: brcdMplsInterfaceRowStatus
brcdMplsInterfaceRowStatus.description: The row status of an entry. Note: Set request to this table is not supported in this release. Always returns 'active' for the existing entries.

mplsConfiguredLsps.name: mplsConfiguredLsps
mplsConfiguredLsps.description: Number of configured LSPs. Sum of RSVP and static configured LSPs. DEPRECATED BY mplsTunnelConfigured IN rfc3812-MPLS-TE-STD-MIB.

mplsActiveLsps.name: mplsActiveLsps
mplsActiveLsps.description: Number of active LSPs. Sum of RSVP, LDP and static LSPs. DEPRECATED BY mplsTunnelActive IN rfc3812-MPLS-TE-STD-MIB.

mplsLspTable.name: mplsLspTable
mplsLspTable.description: List of Configured Label Switched Paths.

mplsLspEntry.name: mplsLspEntry
mplsLspEntry.description: Entry containing information about a particular Label Switched Path.

mplsLspSignalingProto.name: mplsLspSignalingProto
mplsLspSignalingProto.description: MPLS signaling protocol used by this LSP.

mplsLspIndex.name: mplsLspIndex
mplsLspIndex.description: The unique index of the LSP in the system for a given signaling protocol.

mplsLspName.name: mplsLspName
mplsLspName.description: Name of the Label Switched Path.

mplsLspState.name: mplsLspState
mplsLspState.description: The operational state of the LSP.

mplsLspPackets.name: mplsLspPackets
mplsLspPackets.description: The number of egress Layer-3 VPN and IPoMPLS packets meeting the in-label and tunnel criteria.

mplsLspAge.name: mplsLspAge
mplsLspAge.description: The age, since creation of this LSP in 10-millisecond periods.

mplsLspTimeUp.name: mplsLspTimeUp
mplsLspTimeUp.description: The total time in 10-millisecond units that this LSP has been operational. The percentage up time can be determined by computing (mplsLspTimeUp/mplsLspAge * 100 %).

mplsLspPrimaryTimeUp.name: mplsLspPrimaryTimeUp
mplsLspPrimaryTimeUp.description: The total time in 10-millisecond units that this LSP's primary path has been operational. The percentage contribution of the primary path to the operational time is given by (mplsLspPrimaryTimeUp/mplsLspTimeUp * 100) %.

mplsLspTransitions.name: mplsLspTransitions
mplsLspTransitions.description: The number of state transitions (up -> down and down -> up) this LSP has undergone.

mplsLspLastTransition.name: mplsLspLastTransition
mplsLspLastTransition.description: The time in 10-millisecond units since the last transition occurred on this LSP.

mplsLspFrom.name: mplsLspFrom
mplsLspFrom.description: Source IP address of this LSP.

mplsLspTo.name: mplsLspTo
mplsLspTo.description: Destination IP address of this LSP.

mplsLspPathName.name: mplsLspPathName
mplsLspPathName.description: The name of the active path for this LSP, if any. If there is none, the name should be empty; in that case, the rest of the fields in mplsLspEntry are meaningless.

mplsLspPathType.name: mplsLspPathType
mplsLspPathType.description: The type of path that is active, i.e., a primary path, a standby path, or a generic secondary path. This field is meaningless unless mplsLspPathName is not empty

mplsLspAdaptive.name: mplsLspAdaptive
mplsLspAdaptive.description: Indicates if the LSP supports adaptive mechanism or not.

mplsLspBfdSessionId.name: mplsLspBfdSessionId
mplsLspBfdSessionId.description: The BFD session ID associated to this LSP. Zero indicates there is no BFD session for this LSP. Non-zero value is an index to an entry in the bfdSessTable

mplsLspReoptimizeTimer.name: mplsLspReoptimizeTimer
mplsLspReoptimizeTimer.description: The number of seconds from the beginning of one reoptimization attempt to the beginning of the next attempt.

mplsLspCoS.name: mplsLspCoS
mplsLspCoS.description: The Class of Service for this LSP.

mplsLspHopLimit.name: mplsLspHopLimit
mplsLspHopLimit.description: The number of hops this LSP can traverse.

mplsLspCspf.name: mplsLspCspf
mplsLspCspf.description: Indicates if CSPF path calculation is enabled on this LSP.

mplsLspCspfTieBreaker.name: mplsLspCspfTieBreaker
mplsLspCspfTieBreaker.description: The tie-breaker to use for selecting CSPF equal-cost paths. The value of this variable is meaningless if the mplsLspCspf is 'disabled'.

mplsLspFrrMode.name: mplsLspFrrMode
mplsLspFrrMode.description: Indicates which protection method is to be used for Fast Reroute. 'detour' means one-to-one backup and 'facility' for facility backup.

mplsLspFrrSetupPriority.name: mplsLspFrrSetupPriority
mplsLspFrrSetupPriority.description: The setup priority for MPLS Fast Reroute. The value of this variable is meaningless if the mplsLspFrrMode is 'none'.

mplsLspFrrHoldingPriority.name: mplsLspFrrHoldingPriority
mplsLspFrrHoldingPriority.description: The hold priority for MPLS Fast Reroute. The value of this variable is meaningless if the mplsLspFrrMode is 'none'.

mplsLspFrrHopLimit.name: mplsLspFrrHopLimit
mplsLspFrrHopLimit.description: The hop limit for MPLS Fast Reroute. The value of this variable is meaningless if the mplsLspFrrMode is 'none'.

mplsLspFrrBandwidth.name: mplsLspFrrBandwidth
mplsLspFrrBandwidth.description: The bandwidth constraint for MPLS Fast Reroute. The value 0 means that the detour route uses a best-effort value for bandwidth. The value of this variable is meaningless if the mplsLspFrrMode is 'none'.

mplsLspFrrAdmGrpIncludeAny.name: mplsLspFrrAdmGrpIncludeAny
mplsLspFrrAdmGrpIncludeAny.description: The administrative group setting that the device includes any of the interfaces that are members of the group when calculating detour routes for this LSP. The value of this variable is meaningless if the mplsLspFrrMode is 'none'.

mplsLspFrrAdmGrpIncludeAll.name: mplsLspFrrAdmGrpIncludeAll
mplsLspFrrAdmGrpIncludeAll.description: The administrative group setting that an interface must be a member of to be considered in a detour route for the LSP. Any interface that is not a member of all the groups is eliminated from consideration. The value of this variable is meaningless if the mplsLspFrrMode is 'none'.

mplsLspFrrAdmGrpExcludeAny.name: mplsLspFrrAdmGrpExcludeAny
mplsLspFrrAdmGrpExcludeAny.description: The administrative group setting that the device excludes any of the interfaces that are members of the group when calculating detour routes for this LSP. The value of this variable is meaningless if the mplsLspFrrMode is 'none'.

mplsLspPathSelectMode.name: mplsLspPathSelectMode
mplsLspPathSelectMode.description: Indicates the path selection mode to use. Auto-select is the default mode. I this mode, the primary path is always selected to carry traffic when the primary path has stayed operating in the working state for at least the amount of time specified in mplsLspPathSelectRevertTimer. For manual-select, traffic is switched to a user- selected path specified in mplsLspPathSelectPathname after the selected path has stayed operating in the working state for at least the amount of time specified in mplsLspPathSelectRevertTimer. For unconditional-select, traffic is switched to and stays on the selected path regardless of the path's condition even if it is in a failure state.

mplsLspPathSelectPathname.name: mplsLspPathSelectPathname
mplsLspPathSelectPathname.description: The user-selected pathname when the mplsLspPathSelectMode is either 'manual' or 'unconditional'.

mplsLspPathSelectRevertTimer.name: mplsLspPathSelectRevertTimer
mplsLspPathSelectRevertTimer.description: The number of seconds to wait after the primary or selected path comes up before traffic reverts to that path. A value of 0 indicates that it will switch immediately after the current working path goes down.

mplsLspShortcutOspfAllowed.name: mplsLspShortcutOspfAllowed
mplsLspShortcutOspfAllowed.description: Indicates that this LSP allows shortcut between nodes in an AS. OSPF includes the LSP in its SPF calculation.

mplsLspShortcutIsisAllowed.name: mplsLspShortcutIsisAllowed
mplsLspShortcutIsisAllowed.description: Indicates that this LSP allows shortcut through the network to a destination based on the path's cost (metric). Traffic is forwarded through this LSP to destinations within the IS-IS routing domain. IS-IS includes the LSP in its SPF calculation.

mplsLspShortcutIsisLevel.name: mplsLspShortcutIsisLevel
mplsLspShortcutIsisLevel.description: Indicates the level of IS-IS routing enabled on the device. The value of this variable is meaningless if the mplsLspShortcutIsisAllowed is 'false'.

mplsLspShortcutIsisAnnounce.name: mplsLspShortcutIsisAnnounce
mplsLspShortcutIsisAnnounce.description: Indicates that this IS-IS shortcut will be announced or advertised. The metric to announce is specified by mplsLspShortcutIsisAnnounceMetric. The value of this variable is meaningless if the mplsLspShortcutIsisAllowed is 'false'.

mplsLspShortcutIsisAnnounceMetric.name: mplsLspShortcutIsisAnnounceMetric
mplsLspShortcutIsisAnnounceMetric.description: Indicates the metric value to announce for this shortcut. The value of this variable is meaningless if the mplsLspShortcutIsisAnnounce is 'false'. Default value is 10.

mplsLspShortcutIsisRelativeMetric.name: mplsLspShortcutIsisRelativeMetric
mplsLspShortcutIsisRelativeMetric.description: Indicates the relative metric used to compute the LSP cost when announce is not enabled. The value of this variable is meaningless if the mplsLspShortcutIsisAllowed is 'false'.

snMplsLspUp.name: snMplsLspUp
snMplsLspUp.description: An mplsLspUp trap signifies that the specified LSP is up. The current active path for the LSP is mplsLspPathName.

snMplsLspDown.name: snMplsLspDown
snMplsLspDown.description: An mplsLspDown trap signifies that the specified LSP is down, because the current active path mplsLspPathName went down.

snMplsLspChange.name: snMplsLspChange
snMplsLspChange.description: An mplsLspChange trap signifies that the the specified LSP has switched traffic to the new active path 'toLspPath'. The LSP maintains up state before and after the switch over
